obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_740  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper describes the knock-out of GlyT2. Figure 2 plots the glycine uptake in different CNS Regions including brain stem and spinal cord of wild-Type, heterozygous, and homozygous GlyT2-Deficient Mice. Glycine uptake is seen only at brain stem and spinal cord, and is blocked at GlyT2 knock-out.\n\n28/5/2018 Pim\n- The GlyT2 is a known glycine transporter (see additional literature) located in the presynaptic compartment (see SynGO ID #73).. Experimental description: Targeted Disruption of the Mouse GlyT2 Gene" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
